# LIEC Shipping Platform — Reference

This is the deeper engineering reference for the platform. Read [`CLAUDE.md`](CLAUDE.md) first for the agent-oriented primer; read [`plan.mdf`](plan.mdf) for the original product spec. This document is the source of truth for what the system actually does today, how the layers fit together, and where the known gaps are.

---

## 1. Overview

**Purpose.** Internal operations system that tracks customer goods from drop-off in the origin country to handout at the destination. Customers themselves never use the app — only company employees do. Goods travel between four warehouses (Beirut/BEI, Gabon/GAB, China/CHN, Dubai/DXB) inside shared shipment "containers" (one shipment carries packages from many customers).

**What the platform replaces.** Manual Excel sheets, hand-filled commercial invoices (`925_FINAL_INVOICE___PL_GAB.xlsx` was the canonical template), ad-hoc WhatsApp blasts, paper photo logs.

**Tech stack.**

| Layer | Stack |
|---|---|
| Backend | .NET 8, EF Core 8 (Pomelo MySQL), FluentValidation, ClosedXML, BCrypt.Net-Next, SkiaSharp, Twilio 7.x |
| Frontend | React 18, Vite 5, TypeScript 5, MUI 6, React Query 5, Redux Toolkit 2, Axios, React Router 6, react-toastify, dayjs |
| Storage | MySQL (with in-memory EF fallback for dev), Azure Blob Storage (containers `media` + `exports`) |
| Tests | Playwright e2e (frontend only) |

**Repository layout.**

```
liec/
├── backend/ShippingPlatform.Api/
│   ├── Controllers/                  # 15 controllers (Auth, Currencies, Customer, Dev, Exports, GoodType, Lookups, Packages, PricingConfig, Shipments, Stats, Supplier, SupplyOrder, Warehouse, WhatsApp)
│   ├── Business/                     # AuthBusiness, MasterDataBusiness, CustomerBusiness, ShipmentBusiness, PackageBusiness, SupplyOrderBusiness, WhatsAppBusiness, ExportBusiness, UserBusiness, CurrencyBusiness
│   ├── Services/                     # core services (token, blob, refcode, pricing, capacity, photocompliance, watermark, twilio, audit, transitionrules)
│   │   ├── Currency/                 # FxRateService, ShipmentSnapshotService (namespace: Services.FxRates)
│   │   └── Exports/                  # InvoiceTemplateConstants, InvoiceSequenceService, CommercialDocumentBuilder
│   ├── Models/Entities/              # 21 entity classes (one per file)
│   ├── Models/Enums.cs               # 12 enums in one file
│   ├── Data/AppDbContext.cs          # DbSets + OnModelCreating (indexes, precision, cascades)
│   ├── Dtos/ApiDtos.cs               # all DTOs + DtoMap extension methods
│   ├── Validators/RequestValidators.cs
│   └── Migrations/                   # 13 migrations (chronological, see §2)
├── frontend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── api/                      # client.ts + lookup hooks (lookups.ts, currencies.ts)
│   │   ├── pages/                    # one folder per domain
│   │   ├── components/               # reusable (~45 components)
│   │   ├── helpers/rbac.ts           # MODULE_ACCESS + canX helpers
