## 5. Frontend Architecture

### 5.1 Routing + RBAC mapping

[`Protected.tsx`](frontend/src/Protected.tsx) wraps everything in an auth gate (redirects to `/login` if `!isAuthenticated`). Routes are conditionally registered by [`MODULE_ACCESS`](frontend/src/helpers/rbac.ts) — a Field user attempting `/admin/users` directly gets a 404.

[`application.ts`](frontend/src/application.ts) maps modules into four navigation app shells: Operations, Master Data, Communications, Admin. The current sidebar is derived from the modules visible to the user.

| Module | Roles (FE `MODULE_ACCESS`) | Backend gate | Matches? |
|---|---|---|---|
| dashboard | All | All | ✅ |
| shipments / packages | All | All for reads; Admin/Manager for mutations | ✅ |
| customers / pricing | Admin, Manager, Accountant | Admin/Manager for writes | ✅ |
| warehouses / goodTypes | All | Admin/Manager for writes | ✅ |
| suppliers / supplyOrders | Admin, Manager, Accountant | Admin/Manager for writes | ✅ |
| **currencies** | Admin, Manager, Accountant | **Admin** for writes | ⚠️ FE allows Manager/Accountant to *see* the page; backend rejects writes. Page uses `canManageUsers` to gate write UI as a workaround (§9.21). |
| messaging / groupHelper | Admin, Manager, Accountant | Admin/Manager/Accountant | ✅ |
| users | Admin, Manager | Admin (reads), Admin (writes) | ⚠️ Manager can list users; backend rejects mutation attempts. |

### 5.2 Pages catalog

| Route | File | What it does | Primary mutation | Module |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `/ops/dashboard` | `pages/dashboard/DashboardPage.tsx` | Stats counters + missing-photo alerts | none | dashboard |
| `/ops/shipments` | `pages/shipments/ShipmentsPage.tsx` | Filterable shipment list + create | POST `/shipments` | shipments |
| `/ops/shipments/:id` | `pages/shipments/ShipmentDetailPage.tsx` | Detail, capacity, transitions, packages, tracking, WhatsApp campaigns, **FX Snapshots**, exports | many | shipments |
| `/ops/packages` | `pages/packages/PackagesPage.tsx` | List + auto-assign | POST `/packages/auto-assign` | packages |
| `/ops/packages/:id` | `pages/packages/PackageDetailPage.tsx` | Items (Unit + UnitPrice), photos, transitions, pricing overrides | many | packages |
| `/master/customers` | `CustomersPage.tsx` + `CustomerDetailPage.tsx` | CRUD + WhatsApp consent | POST/PUT | customers |
| `/master/warehouses` | `WarehousesPage.tsx` | CRUD | POST/PUT | warehouses |
| `/master/good-types` | `GoodTypesPage.tsx` | CRUD (bilingual labels) | POST/PUT | goodTypes |
| `/master/pricing-configs` | `PricingConfigsPage.tsx` | CRUD + Activate/Retire | POST/PUT + lifecycle | pricing |
| `/master/suppliers` | `SuppliersPage.tsx` | CRUD | POST/PUT | suppliers |
| `/master/supply-orders` | `SupplyOrdersPage.tsx` | CRUD + lifecycle | POST/PUT + transitions | supplyOrders |
| **`/master/currencies`** | `CurrenciesPage.tsx` | CRUD; IsBase toggle hides Anchor/Rate | POST/PUT/DELETE | currencies |
| `/comms/messaging-logs` | `MessagingLogsPage.tsx` | Campaigns + delivery logs | none | messaging |
| `/comms/group-helper-export` | `GroupHelperExportPage.tsx` | CSV/VCF export | POST | groupHelper |
| `/admin/users` | `UsersPage.tsx` | CRUD users (Admin) | POST/PUT | users |

Inline shipment-detail subsection: **`FxSnapshotsSection`** ([`pages/shipments/components/FxSnapshotsSection.tsx`](frontend/src/pages/shipments/components/FxSnapshotsSection.tsx)) — table of snapshots, "Override Rate" button (Manager+), Edit/Delete on Manual rows.

### 5.3 Reusable components

| Component | Path | Role |
|---|---|---|
| `EnhancedTable` | `components/enhanced-table/` | Sortable/filterable/paginated table; column types TEXT, NUMBER, DATE, COLORED_CHIP, Clickable, Action |
| `DynamicFormWidget` | `components/dynamic-widget/` | Renders form from field config. Field types: TEXT, NUMBER (now supports `step`), SELECT, DATE, CHECKBOX, TEXTAREA, PHONE, EMAIL, FILE, IMAGE. `onFieldChange` callback enables conditional visibility (used in `CurrenciesPage` to hide Anchor/Rate when IsBase). |
| `InformationWidget` | `components/information-widget/` | Read-only field grid |
| `GenericDialog` | `components/GenericDialog/` | MUI Dialog wrapper |
| `MainPageSection` / `DetailPageLayout` / `PageActionsSection` | `components/layout-components/` | Page chrome |
| `PhotoGallery` / `MediaStageCards` / `MediaViewerModal` | `components/media/` | Photo display + lightbox |
| `PricingOverrideHistory` | `components/pricing/` | Override audit trail table |
| `WhatsAppCampaignCards` | `pages/shipments/components/` | Campaign launcher per type |

### 5.4 API client

[`api/client.ts`](frontend/src/api/client.ts) wraps Axios. Helpers: `getJson`, `postJson`, `putJson`, `patchJson`, `uploadMultipart`, `parseApiError`. Request interceptor injects `Authorization: Bearer ${token}` from localStorage; response interceptor logs out on 401.

Lookup hooks: `useUnitsLookup` (in [`api/lookups.ts`](frontend/src/api/lookups.ts)), `useCurrenciesLookup` and `useCurrenciesQuery` (in [`api/currencies.ts`](frontend/src/api/currencies.ts)). Both lookups use `staleTime: Infinity`. The non-lookup `useCurrenciesQuery` does not — see §9.22.

### 5.5 Display conventions

- **Weight** displayed in **tons** (kg/1000, 3 decimals). Inputs are still kg.
- **Volume** labeled **CBM** (never m³ in tables; m³ shows up only in some long-form invoice text).
- **Field ordering**: CBM before Weight everywhere — tables, detail pages, Excel exports.
- **Currency display**: `PackageItem.UnitPrice` always renders `$ X.XX` (USD assumed). The package-level `Currency` field is shown as raw text in the InformationWidget but is otherwise inert (§9.8). `formatCurrencyNumber` is hardcoded to USD locale (§9.20).
- **Status chips** colored from `constants/statusColors.ts`; labels from `constants/statusLabels.ts`.

---

## 6. State Machines

State validation is split between [`Services/TransitionRules.cs`](backend/ShippingPlatform.Api/Services/TransitionRules.cs) (the allowed-transition matrix) and [`Business/OperationsBusiness.cs`](backend/ShippingPlatform.Api/Business/OperationsBusiness.cs) (the business gates).

### 6.1 Shipment

```
Draft → Scheduled → ReadyToDepart → Departed → Arrived → Closed
   └──→ Cancelled (from Draft or Scheduled only)
```

Gate-by-transition:

| Transition | Pre-conditions |
|---|---|
| Draft → Scheduled | TIIU code present and matches regex `^[A-Z]{3,4}\d{4,7}$` |
| Scheduled → ReadyToDepart | At least one package with `Status >= ReadyToShip`; **side-effect:** unloaded packages auto-reassigned |
| ReadyToDepart → Departed | Photo gate: every package has Departure media; **side-effect:** FX snapshot + `ActualDepartureAt` |
| Departed → Arrived | None at the rule level; **side-effect:** FX snapshot + `ActualArrivalAt` |
| Arrived → Closed | Photo gate: every package HandedOut/Cancelled and has Arrival media |
| Draft/Scheduled → Cancelled | **side-effect:** all non-shipped packages cascade to Cancelled |

### 6.2 Package

```
Draft → Received → Packed → ReadyToShip → Shipped → ArrivedAtDestination → ReadyForHandout → HandedOut
  └─────────────────────→ Cancelled (from Draft/Received/Packed/ReadyToShip)
```

| Transition | Pre-conditions |
|---|---|
| Draft → Received | None (or auto-fired by SO `DeliveredToWarehouse`) |
| Received → Packed | `WeightKg > 0`, `Cbm > 0`, ≥1 PackageItem; `PricingService.RecalculateAsync` runs; `CapacityService.RecalculateAsync` runs |
| Packed → ReadyToShip | Shipment status ≥ Scheduled. Items become locked (`PACKAGE_LOCKED` on edit). |
| ReadyToShip → Shipped | Shipment status ≥ Departed; `checkDepartureGate=true` (per-package) |
| Shipped → ArrivedAtDestination | Shipment status ≥ Arrived |
| ArrivedAtDestination → ReadyForHandout | None |
| ReadyForHandout → HandedOut | `checkArrivalGate=true` |
| Cancel | **side-effect:** unlinks supply order, recalculates capacity |

### 6.3 SupplyOrder

```
Draft → Approved → Ordered → DeliveredToWarehouse → PackedIntoPackage → Closed
  └─→ Cancelled (any state, requires reason)
```

| Transition | Side-effects |
|---|---|
| Ordered → DeliveredToWarehouse | Linked package auto-promoted Draft → Received |
| → PackedIntoPackage | Requires `PackageId != null` |
| → Cancelled | Unlinks `PackageId`; package's `SupplyOrderId` cleared |

### 6.4 Gate enforcement summary

| Endpoint | Gate ran |
|---|---|
| `POST /shipments/{id}/depart` | `MissingForShipmentDepartureAsync` |
| `POST /shipments/{id}/close` | `MissingForShipmentCloseAsync` |
| `POST /packages/{id}/ship` | per-package departure check (`checkDepartureGate=true`) |
| `POST /packages/{id}/handout` | `MissingForPackageHandoutAsync` |

All return HTTP 409 with `{ code: "PHOTO_GATE_FAILED", message, missing: [...] }` on failure.

---

## 7. Configuration & Deployment

### 7.1 Config keys

Read in [`Program.cs`](backend/ShippingPlatform.Api/Program.cs) and `appsettings.json`.

| Key | Default | Risk |
|---|---|---|
| `ConnectionStrings:MySql` | (in-memory `shipping` DB) | Embedded in committed config in many setups (§9.3) |
| `Auth:Secret` | `"dev-secret-super-long"` | **Critical fallback** — see §9.1 |
| `AllowedOrigins` | `["http://localhost:5173"]` | CORS-only |
| `Twilio:AccountSid` / `AuthToken` / `WhatsAppFrom` | empty | Empty → DI swaps to `StubWhatsAppSender` ✅ |
| `AzureBlob:ConnectionString` | (often embedded) | §9.3 |
| `AzureBlob:MediaContainer` / `ExportsContainer` | `"media"` / `"exports"` | |
| `AzureBlob:PublicBaseUrl` | empty | **Dead config** — declared but never read (§9.29) |
| `SeedAdmin:Email` / `Password` | env `ADMIN_EMAIL`/`PASSWORD` or `admin@local`/`Admin123!` | Predictable default password (§9.2) |
| `CapacityThresholdPct` | 80 | UI warning threshold only |
| `InvoiceTemplate:DefaultFreight` | 2550 | Single tunable value (rate fields removed, now sourced from snapshots) |

### 7.2 Startup behavior

```
1. db.Database.Migrate()
2. Seed admin (always — checks email exists first)
3. Seed warehouses (4 default if Warehouses empty)
4. Seed good types (12 default)
5. Seed pricing config (1 default if empty: "Standard Rate 2025", EUR)
6. SeedHelper.SeedCustomers(db) — 20 default customers + WhatsApp consents
7. SeedHelper.SeedCurrencies(db) — USD/EUR/XAF
```

Any of the seed steps no-ops if its target table already has rows.

### 7.3 Dev reset

`POST /api/dev/reset-data` (Admin + `IsDevelopment()` guard, 404 otherwise) — wipes Shipments, Packages, PackageItems, Media, Suppliers, SupplyOrders, Campaigns, DeliveryLogs, AuditLogs, ShipmentSequences, Customers, WhatsAppConsents, plus their snapshots. Then re-runs `SeedCustomers` and `SeedCurrencies`. Preserves AdminUsers, Warehouses, GoodTypes, PricingConfigs, Currencies (because the seed re-runs but only inserts when empty).

