## 9. Gaps & Risks

Comprehensive inventory from a multi-angle audit. Each item: title, location, severity, recommended fix.

### 9.1–9.5 Critical (security)

**9.1 JWT secret fallback.** [`Program.cs`](backend/ShippingPlatform.Api/Program.cs) defaults `Auth:Secret` to `"dev-secret-super-long"` if config is unset. Production deploy without the env var = trivially forgeable tokens. **Fix:** throw on startup unless `Environment.IsDevelopment()`.

**9.2 Predictable default admin password.** Same file seeds the bootstrap admin with `Admin123!` if `SeedAdmin:Password` is unset. **Fix:** require an env var; refuse to start otherwise.

**9.3 Secrets embedded in `appsettings.json`.** MySQL connection string and Azure Blob connection string can leak via committed config. **Fix:** move to env vars, Azure Key Vault, or managed identity.

**9.4 No password reset / lockout / MFA.** `AdminUser` has only `PasswordHash`. No reset token, no email flow, no failed-attempt lockout (just a 10/min rate-limit on the login endpoint). **Fix:** add `/auth/forgot-password` + email link, add `FailedLoginCount` + `LockedUntil` to the entity.

**9.5 Audit-log GET endpoint role-gating unclear.** `GET /api/shipments/{id}/audit-log` ([`ShipmentsController.cs:84-85`](backend/ShippingPlatform.Api/Controllers/ShipmentsController.cs#L84-L85)) inherits the global `RequireAuthorization` but has no per-method `[Authorize(Roles=...)]`. Confirm intent — Field shouldn't necessarily see audit; tighten to `[Authorize(Roles="Admin,Manager")]`.

### 9.6–9.18 High (data integrity / business logic)

**9.6 RefCodeService + InvoiceSequenceService race conditions.** Both do `read → increment → SaveChangesAsync` without a lock. Two concurrent calls can both read N and both save N+1. The unique index on `(OriginWarehouseCode, Year)` / `Year` will throw on the second commit, but the caller sees an exception rather than a clean retry. **Fix:** wrap in a `SERIALIZABLE` transaction or use `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` with Pomelo's raw-SQL escape hatch.

**9.7 `PricingConfig.Currency` and `Package.Currency` are not foreign-keyed to `Currencies.Code`.** A config can reference `"EUR"` even after the EUR currency is deleted. **Fix:** add an FK or a CHECK at write time.

**9.8 `Package.Currency` is semantically dead.** `PricingService` sets it from the active pricing config (defaulting to `"EUR"`), the `InformationWidget` displays it, but `PackageItem.UnitPrice` is now always USD by contract. The currency string on the package no longer reflects the unit-price units. **Fix:** rename to `Package.PricingCurrency` (still meaningful for the freight charge) and explain in tooltips, or hide in the UI.

**9.9 `ShipmentSnapshotService.ResolveForInvoiceAsync` returns synthetic snapshots tagged `Event=Manual`.** The live-fallback path constructs a `ShipmentRateSnapshot { Event = Manual }` that's not persisted. Caller can't tell user-entered overrides apart from live-computed fallbacks. **Fix:** add a `Live` enum value, or return a discriminated `(snapshot, source)` record, or change return type to a dedicated `ResolvedRate`.

**9.10 Frontend role allowlist not enforced server-side for package transitions.** `FIELD_PKG_TRANSITIONS = {receive, pack, ready-to-ship}` is a FE-only constraint. Backend `[Authorize(Roles="Admin,Manager,Field")]` is blanket. A Field user could `POST /api/packages/{id}/ship` directly and the gate would only stop them via the photo-gate or status-precondition. **Fix:** per-action role table on the backend (e.g., `Ship` requires `Admin,Manager`).

**9.11 `PackageItem.UnitPrice` arbitrary default of 10.** `AddItemAsync` substitutes `10m` when null. Pretty arbitrary — no audit trail saying "10 was the default", no tooltip in the UI explaining it. **Fix:** make it required at the DTO level, OR default to 0, OR allow null all the way (most semantically honest, and the invoice builder already handles null).

**9.12 F8 cell semantic shift undocumented.** Legacy `925_FINAL_INVOICE___PL_GAB.xlsx` had `1.3496503` hardcoded in F8. New code passes `EurPerBase` (≈ 1.075) into the same cell. Anyone with the legacy `.xlsx` open as a reference will see different math. **Fix:** add a tooltip / cell comment in the workbook explaining the source, document in the export README.

**9.13 `AuditLog` coverage incomplete.** Currently only Shipment and Package status transitions are logged. Currency CRUD, FX overrides, pricing-config activate/retire, user role changes, media uploads, and login attempts (success/fail/IP) are unlogged. **Fix:** add `audit.LogAsync(...)` at each mutation point. Compliance gap if the platform ever needs to be audited externally.

**9.14 `Media.RecordedByAdminUserId` never populated.** Field exists; every upload path leaves it `default(int) = 0`. **Fix:** populate from `User.GetUserId()` in the upload handler. Also no FK to `AdminUser` — add one.

**9.15 `WhatsAppDeliveryLog.Result = Pending` rows never flip async.** The synchronous bulk-send loop sets Sent/Failed inline. If the loop is interrupted (process kill, exception mid-loop), Pending rows stay Pending forever. **Fix:** background reconciliation job, or mark stale Pendings as Failed on next campaign launch.

**9.16 `CapacityService.RecalculateAsync` runs after every package change.** N+1 risk on bulk transitions: `BulkTransitionAsync` recomputes capacity per package. **Fix:** batch the recalc once at the end of the bulk operation.

**9.17 `Shipment.MaxWeightKg` / `MaxCbm` not validated against `Warehouse.MaxWeightKg` / `MaxCbm`.** A shipment can be sized larger than its origin warehouse's capacity. The capacity bars are advisory only (UI warnings, no hard reject). **Fix:** validate on shipment create and update, return 400 if `Shipment.Max* > origin Warehouse.Max*`.

**9.18 Mutable `List<>` exposed on entity DTOs.** `Package.Items`, `Package.Media`, `Package.PricingOverrides` are mutable. Callers that hold a reference can mutate them and break invariants. **Fix:** project to immutable DTOs, or change entity properties to `IReadOnlyList<>`.

### 9.19–9.29 Medium (UX / consistency / observability)

**9.19 `labelAr` returned by lookups but never used.** `useUnitsLookup` and `useCurrenciesLookup` both surface `labelAr`; no FE component renders it. **Fix:** implement an i18n framework (e.g., `react-i18next`) or drop the field from the API contract.

**9.20 `formatCurrencyNumber` hardcoded to USD.** [`helpers/formatting-utils.ts`](frontend/src/helpers/formatting-utils.ts) calls `Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD' })` regardless of the input currency. **Fix:** accept an optional `currency` param (defaulting to USD) so the multi-currency data can be formatted correctly.

**9.21 `CurrenciesPage` uses `canManageUsers` for write-gating.** Semantic mismatch — currencies aren't user management. **Fix:** add `canManageCurrencies` helper to [`helpers/rbac.ts`](frontend/src/helpers/rbac.ts) (Admin only) aligned with the backend's `[Authorize(Roles="Admin")]`.

**9.22 `useCurrenciesQuery` missing `staleTime: Infinity`.** Used by the CRUD page (which can mutate, so it does need re-fetch). But every focus event triggers a re-query. **Fix:** keep the default for the CRUD page itself but make sure other consumers prefer `useCurrenciesLookup`. Acceptable as-is.

**9.23 `parseApiError` not used in `ItemDialog`.** Generic `'Add item failed'` toast instead of `parseApiError(e).message`. Other pages use the latter. **Fix:** standardize.

**9.24 No error boundaries on the frontend.** An unhandled error in any page crashes the whole app. **Fix:** add a top-level `<ErrorBoundary>` in `App.tsx` that renders a graceful fallback.

**9.25 Pagination missing on Customers / Suppliers / SupplyOrders / Warehouses / Users / GoodTypes.** Only Shipments + Packages paginate. Will hurt at scale. **Fix:** add `?page=` + `?pageSize=` query params, mirror the Shipments pattern.

**9.26 No tests for new features.** Currencies CRUD, FX Snapshots section, Unit/UnitPrice on items, Commercial Invoice + Packing List export. **Fix:** add Playwright specs.

**9.27 Validators missing for `UpdateShipmentRequest`, `ShipmentTrackingSyncRequest`, `SupplyOrderTransitionRequest`.** These pass through controllers without FluentValidation. Validation logic lives in the business layer instead. **Fix:** add FluentValidation classes to keep the validation pattern uniform.

**9.28 Empty states inconsistent across list pages.** Some show "No X found", some show empty rows. **Fix:** standardize via a shared empty-state component.

**9.29 `AzureBlob:PublicBaseUrl` declared but never read.** Dead config. **Fix:** either implement custom-domain URL rewriting or drop the key.

### 9.30–9.36 Low (tech debt)

**9.30 `ShipmentSnapshotEvent.Manual` overloaded.** See §9.9 — also worth a comment in the enum file.

**9.31 ClosedXML 0.103 → 0.104 NuGet warning.** `.csproj` pins `>= 0.103.0`; only 0.104 resolves. **Fix:** bump constraint.

**9.32 No retry on Azure Blob upload.** Transient network failures bubble up. **Fix:** add Polly + exponential backoff.

**9.33 `RefCodeService` uses `year % 100`.** Clear but `year.ToString("yy")` reads better.

**9.34 No CSRF protection.** Acceptable for Bearer-token auth (cookies aren't used) but worth documenting so external auditors don't flag it as a finding.

**9.35 Mobile responsiveness untested.** No formal breakpoint plan, no mobile-targeted Playwright spec.

**9.36 Accessibility sparse.** Labels, keyboard nav, color contrast not audited. WCAG conformance unknown.

